caption: Appa ji is really one of the best resturant manager in the hotel. Not only did he serve us heartily but also took our photos. The hotel is one of the best. I always make a night halt in this while traveling from pune to bhopal. Pure veg, no non sense people. Clean and spacious. Amazing food. Great hotel!

Hotel did not give room to me Becuase of maintenance issue On the floor as this was Royal suit so I booked Superior room as after discussion with manager he said royal suit amount will refund you.. On same date I booked 2 rooms and 2 times full payment by make my trip.. Now make my trip not responding for amount and no refunded by hotel...
Hotel is very good, staff is good but little lazy in room service. Food is amazing and Chef is an excellent person.

average good, good ambience with worst staff and their attitude. they behave as they owning a 5start hotel but in reality they treat clients like a roadside dhaba.  i have a video proof of that staff who was taking order, will post it on Youtube As ' Chapri Staff Of Jhankar Palace'
Kudos to whole hotel staff and specially restaurant.. food was amazing and service was above few so called 5*
The rooms and room service was good. Ample space outside. Recommended for stay and functions.
The room was full of cockroaches and when I complained they provided me a hit to kill them. In morning there was no water and we had to wait for 2 hours to get it fixed.

Nice property at Dhule. Rooms were spacious , neat and clean. Food was delicious served hot even in late night. Staff was cooperative. Only issue was with lift which was too slow. Property owner should add one more lift in the hotel.

Firstly they should mention their hotel's full name on the map. Because of wrong name i got to the wrong address.... Rooms were great...but the hotel needs some renovations in common areas like sofas and lift...
The room was full of insects and no water in the morning to bath. You will get many other good options in the same budget.

Had visited Amalner, Jalgaon for a business visit and could bot find a single decent and hygienic place to stay in Amalner. That's when someone suggested this place in Dhule which is about an hours drive and it was truely a saviour. Offers decent rooms, food and service. Location is good and is just adjacent to Mumbai highway. The price tag is decent as well!

Staff is lethargic and inattentive....No tissues, dental kit and food menu... place for breakfast is not denoted and will make you search atleast for 5 mins... Ground floor of the adjacent property was stinking....only 1 lift available.... Breakfast was limited and Ok... Breakfast service was poor... Surprisingly, room dine in was amazing.... I was asked for the full payment without checking the pre book status.

Worst Staff, average food, person who takes order is very arrogant. I request hotel owners to come as a guest sometime to check the attitude of der staff or workers everymonth. Jhankar palace staff is now really worse. They are degrading the image of hotel.
After a tiring road journey, it was a pleasure to walk into a neat and clean hotel with nice ambience, courteous and smiling staff and good food.
Rooms quality is not good Rooms are ok ok Service good but price of room doesn't sute room

Service not good and Room had one or another maintenance issues whether it be standard room or royal suite.I stayed in 1st week of Dec 2021,it was peak of wedding time in this vicinity and this property so no proper hot water.This hot water issues is been there since past 1 year and more.  Staff was polite but lack a bit of professional approach specially may be because of  unwanted intervention by hotel owner in day to day operations.  I saw him shouting at one young lady stating this is my property and you can leave.This type of behavior does not reciprocate an owner approach.  All in all not a good stay for business trip because everytime you will see entire new staff(may be because of owner not giving them proper facilities/salaries) but due to limited options in Dhule, travellers usually goes there but have heard that 2-3 premium competitors are coming up with new venture in the vicinity.
Overpriced executive rooms in terms of standards & amenities. Breakfast is below sub standard. Very poor condition of the bathrooms. Would not recommend at all.
Harish Ji was excellent manager An epitome of a manager. Highly appreciated service.
Located near Dhule Gurudwara on Mumbai Agra road (service road junction). Hotel room is specious n clean. Bathroom needs deep cleaning. Only veg food, no bar or nonveg. Secure parking.
Amazing service and hospitality by the breakfast team Chef Harish ji …. Thankyou for the on request quick service

I felt this is a marriage garden and not a hotel. Staff is not professionally trained the way you will find generally in hotel industry. so if you are used to staying in hotels and expecting some level of service, forget it. Few experiences from my stay during weekend 20th-Nov-2021. 1. If you don't have an option and had to choose this hotel, ensure that you have room rates agreed in writing with all details. Don't believe phone conversation. Once you land there they will give some reasons(if you miss getting in writing) and charge you heavy(may be double as well) 2. They have very old ACs, pale yellow colour. ACs will make noise as if water cooler. If you are lucky it will cool also. 3. Even if you have to stay in absence of choice, DO NOT eat here. Very pathetic room service. We waited for 50 minutes for tea and one room got tea (out of 3 rooms we booked), if you see the tea cattle, it looked like not washed for few months. Our member who drank that tea vomited after some time. 4. Some rooms are of good size but they will confuse you with type of rooms so see the rooms and check for yourself before confirming on rates. 5. Bathroom showers are not cleaned for ages so its scaled & jam. You need to use bucket only. Property will look good in pictures and i think people get deceived because of that. I felt its not worth as its overall poorly managed with unhygenic (food).

Pros: Nice Hotel. Look spacious Easy to locate. Near highway. Ambience is great. Room are maintained properly and cleaned. All staffs were polite and nice.  Cons: Major water problems as lot of times water supply wasn't in place due to which we face lot of issues. Geysers were not working properly. Price for tea and coffee is very high. They charge 50Rs per tea.  Compared to all other hotels in Dhule , this hotel is quite much better in terms of ambience, spacious rooms with dedicated lifts.
One of the best options for stay in Dhule. Clean rooms, ample parking space, and tasty food. Buffet breakfast could have had more options.
Too costly and the rooms are not worth the price. Sub bar breakfast and cleanliness. Cockroaches running around in the breakfast hall. Doesn't recommend for this higher price.

Nice huge place with a all vegetarian restaurant. Helpful and friendly staff which is always ready to help out. This place is also used for hosting marriages. Can hear some amount of noise in the night since it is next to the highway.
The ambiance was great. The waiting staff was professional and proficient at the same time. The food was absolutely delicious and by far the tastiest I've had in the city.

Been here for a night , was occupying twin bed rooms. Hotel is neat and clean and has ample parking & also safe. Owner stays in adjacent bunglow only. We were traveling on our motorcycles and were concerned a bit about its safety. even with ample parking in hotel owner was very courteous and offered us to park our bike in his home parking and this was very welcoming. Best part if this is bang on highway , so if you want to just stay for a night then this place is perfectly situated for all travellers, A tad bit on the expensive side is what we felt but then its still worth the money.

Perhaps the best hotel in Dhule at present - year 2021.  Well appointed rooms, great food (pure vegetarian only) and good parking under CCTV camera surveillance are some of the highlights of this hotel.  All covid precautions were taken by the staff during our stay. We happened to meet the owner too who is a very kind person.
It was nice experience to have Breakfast

If you are traveling on Mumbai - Agra road and plan to halt for a night near Dhule then  this is a descent place for family to stay. They have clean and good size rooms . Room service is efficient. They have a veg restaurant with good ambience and serves delicious food.You also have option for Jain food on request. I would like to personally thank the owner & staff  of this property who has maintained the standards at par with good hotels in metros.

Good place, rooms are ok, hot water issue as the hotel uses Solar for water heating. It take pretty long time for hot water to flow. Toilets suck. Ambiance is good. Good for family stay if u can compromise on bathroom.

Have been staying here since it was opened as Jhankar palace. It is still the best place to stay in  dhule. However it needs a good amount of renovation now. Rooms are standard, washrooms have detoriated in last 01 year. Food quality is very good. Vegetarian traveller's would love it. No non veg food allowed.

Worst experience. There were No tandoori, no Chinese, no Roti's, no naan items in the hotel at all. Waited for 30mins but didn't receive any order from the staff. At the end we cancelled all the order and left.  Please avoid to visit the restaurant. Worst experience. 😡😡 …

Pros  Very neat and clean room  Nice food  Courteous staff  They even entertained me when I wanted room to be sanitised in my presence.  Cons  Located on highway so might get disturbing in night for some  people
Rooms were in okayish condition. No proper hot water, insects in the room and outside the window. Too expensive for this kind of service and facilities.  Food is not bad. Good place for events.

Very good hotel in Dhule... Location is bang on highway and with good visibility. Very clean and spacious rooms. They also have variety in rooms.  Food - Awesome veg food.... Must try without fail. Just make sure you order less since they serve huge quality...They also serves jain food.  But if there is marriage or any party in the lawns behind then it may be noisy but still manageable...

Enroute Aurangabad to Ahmedabad, halted for lunch. A local reference took us to this place.  Pleased by the wide array of indian and continental food fusion menu. Tried indo-chinese fusion food that turned out too well and mouthwatering.  So quality tasty food with nice ambience and seating arrangement coupled by prompt services makes this a good place for a travel break enroute.  Visible from main road has ample parking.  A more helpful reception staff is requested that properly guides or shows the way to restaurant.  Overall this place is a pride for dhule and hope they upkeep their standards.  Enjoy.

Worst hotel of all time. No one helped us to carry our luggage, no support from reception area, extremely unprofessional behaviour by the front desk manager. Had to literally wait for an hour to get tea and the AC was not working in a super deluxe room. 3000 rupees in drain. Would literally give it a zero star.
Only one disadvantages It's just on side of main high way.  Whole night vehicles run continue. Not recommended for nicely sleeping persons.
It was quit good the food was osam and comfortable
No hot water for bathing Not proper room service Not proper breakfast

Good place. I stayed in Executive Room and found it to be decent. They won't have  some utilities such as iron box. Staff is polite and courteous. Food is decent. Pleaseully check bills. There could be minor errors. It's not intentional. The staff is mistake prone it seems.

The place has been renovated in last months of 2018 and has a differently abled friendly porch and lobby with parking. The interiors of the lobby are great. A banquet hall accomodating around 400 people is also open. As told an open air garden restaurant 'under the been would open soon. Also a conference room and restaurant is opening soon in the new building.

This is one of the best hotel in dhule city. Cleanliness and hygiene is maintained. But break fast food is not good quality.  They are not provided fress items. They only heating old prepared items and served to customers hence test is not good due to refrying/reheating.
Best Hotel in Dhule. Staff is Cooperative and Polite. Nice food with beautiful ambience.

Had been there for friends wedding. Partly ready. Rooms are ready and good. Open area for wedding is beautiful. Easy access for people traveling by bus from outstation. Good food. Only drawback I felt was that the staff is not well trained.
Excellent place to stay. Nice restaurant. Definately will stay again if needed.

Good hotel in dhule Rooms are good One need to be careful for here Mosquitos Even though hotel is managing but too much mosquitoes. Restaurant is awesome here Its pure and only veg hotel.  Just besides gurudwara on main mumbai Agra highway.

Good Hotel, Nice and comfortable rooms, under construction though, might get better. Convenient location. But lacks some basics like complementary Breakfast, must be because the restaurant is separate and the guests type being a hotel in town. But, overall its Good and recommend for a comfortable stay in Dhule.

Great to stay here. All staff are friendly, helpful and well maintained. They are strictly following the rules and regulations made-up by their management which makes them great in hospitality. 👏👍 Be careful don't bring Non-veg and Alcohol inside the hotel premises, it is strictly prohibited.
Not worth the money you will spend, the rooms are strictly okay and food is horrendous with charges double than any metro hotel. Strictly NOT recommended
Good place for a night Halt. Little expensive though.

An okay okay hotel. Rooms are very small and unexpected size and washrooms are too small which don't allow you to turnaround...too big restaurant for this hotel but horrible breakfast menu. Laterally nothing and unhealthy atmosphere and quality of food... Don't expect much over here foenthe cost you pay...
Interior was fascinating ... Ambience was good 👍🏻
Positive hotel wit amazing restaurant. They made us try new variety papad and all their food in menu is pretty delicious. Very nice stay. Still construction goin on but a was a good experience.

Horrible complimentary breakfast. Arrogant dinning Hall staff. You will not get to complain to the managers as they are not available.   And surprise.. Surprise... The c card 💳 machine doesnot work and you need to keep cash handy. …
Excellent ambiance and very good food. Maintenance is a grey area of this hotel. There are leaking taps/showers. Bathroom fittings, though new, are not cleaned properly.

i have stayed here once and had lunch twice. Rooms are Good but service is pathetic. food taste is ok. Giving three stars because its in Dhule where you dont have much more options... otherwise I would have rated it 2
Room was not cleaned properly. There was no Hot water in toilet. Service was very poor. Air conditioner was third class.
This place is comfortably located near the highway. Offers nice rooms for stay. Restaurants like Oregano are hard to find in Dhule, it's a clean and fairly priced restaurant. Vegetarian meals only.
Food at restaurant is good, breakfast has very limited items and below par .. very average,  rooms are pathetic and very small, sad bathrooms

Worst experience of my touring life stayed at This Hotel... No proper water flow in tap, room service very very poor... Very casual attitude of Hotel Staff.  Guys thing before you choose this hotel. I will not suggest anyone yo stay here  But i must say Food Quality is Superb

You don't have choice in Dhule to stay so this hotel rooms are good but Morning break fast is boring same menu daily. You don't get bottle water after 10:30 Pm. Ab vo khawat hai na Majboori ka naam .......... waisi chiz hai bus but nice ambience.
Very good hotel, problem with hot water, have to waste lots of water and then hot water come.. we almost open tap for half an hr. Then we get hot water, when we say save water this is very bad..
Good stay and good food, but I needed to ask for complementary tea and cofee kit along with electric cattle

Pros Very neat and clean room Nice food Courteous staff They even entertained me when I wanted room to be sanitised in my presence.  Cons Located on highway so might get disturbing in night for some people
Nice place Good Services And Good Parking Place Available In This Hotel All a stay AC rooms Are Superb
Good food .... Good services and also good ambience

Love it i go there with my friends and enjoy it lot the paji is very free mind person and his nature is sooo good and the food is also too good we eat paneer tikka and paneer masala there after this we also eat a treat there which is soo delicious and i  keep going on this place with and my one of the friend suggested me the place to go so nice and loveable place visit it

Worst place, please do not visit. You order something and after sometime they will come and say not available. Worst experience. Half of the menu items are not available. After waiting 40 mins, we cancelled the order and left the place.
I had been in banquet hall.. Nice to arrange programme.. Food quality good
I have been traveling to Dhule since last 1 year, I can bet you will not get better hotel to stay than Hotel JP Kyriad ( Jhankar palace )
Great Food.....Awesome staff!!!!

it was a family function and yet those people had no idea that some day it will be over flooded with 100's of people and had no clue how to handle the Hotel service and yet management also pathetic with that much of expense! If you even visit this city this Hotel least suggested.
We had 2 days booking for weeding. The service given by the hotel team was good.
Nice place in town to visit for Dinner. Also, a good venue for small functions if anyone want to host in town.

Good staff, Good service, Good food, Good room, Decent n clean washroom but a tile was broken. Bang on the highway next to Gurudwara. Breakfast spread was limited. Room charges a bit high for this pkace
Good Place to stay, but the Tarif is on higher end comparing the facilities one gets. They need a Good Manager to handle the staff who are good but lack training. All in all good stay.
Nice place with amazing staff and prompt service. The food here is really good. Can stay with family. Spacious and luxurious rooms
Below average rooms i.e 208, improper main door lock (room no. 212) terrible food especially upma xD, no proper WiFi connectivity, poor room service

Very bad experience.. it is too costly.. last year we had visited we experienced a good hospitality so this year we visit again with full family but we are not at all satisfied with the service and food was pathetic

Not surprised. Because it is a small town, I should set my expectations low but I could not prevent myself from laughing when I saw the a small wooden partition in the curtain holder!  It prevented me from closing the two panels of the curtains completely.  The very purpose of having curtains was defeated.
The hotal has to much place to play on ground. So we. Should visit once for playing. Cricket
Due to the nature of Monopoly in Dhule district, this hotel is able to survive. Pathetic service and worst food. Every time at breakfast I have to literally fight to get hot food. Limited varieties.
The hotel is a nice option for an overnight stay. It's not too far from the city and easy to locate. The rooms are clean and maintained. This is probably the best place you can stay at in Dhule.
Best hotel in area. For families, solo travelers and business personals. Total value for money. They can improve their menu though
Don't expect great services. They don't provide water bottles. Pretty boring place. Inflated restaurant prices. Cannot compare to places in bigger cities. But you cannot find better places in Dhule.
Its an 100% vegetarian food taste is really good bit costly but worthy restaurant and hotel rooms pretty nice I was here for more then 10days visit once
Inflexible staff, limited breakfast options, WiFi and some amenities advertised don't work but good rooms. Not value for money. Wouldn't recommend for business travellers
Very nice hotel to stay. Cleanliness, hospitality and food are excellent. Such type of hotel in this remote area is appreciated. Enjoyed stay
Nice place for Ceremony, stay
Booked delux room for one night stay for 1500 bucks, dusty room, no drinking water, not even given whn asked for. Smthing biting whole night in d quilt. Not value for money.

Hotel jhankar is on good place but there is no board on road, so we can't understand where is jhankar hotel, we need to see google map to find it, Service is good no problem with service and rooms are average, main problem there is no board on agra road , so we can't easily understand where is jhankar hotel
Wonderful place for stay. The food is simply amazing.  I will suggest this hotel to everyone who wants to have a stay in Dhule. Great going team Jhankar Palace
On our way back to Nashik, we were looking for a place to stop for breakfast. Went to this hotel which is conveniently located on the highway. Surprisingly it was good where we had a good breakfast
New hotel. Neat and clean but bathrooms are not maintained properly. Sufficient place for marriage functions and parking.
One of the best and newest hotels in Dhule. Located a little away from the main market and near the Mumbai highway it's a pure veg hotel.
Best hotel for Non-vegetarian n families traveling through NH-3 . Room service n Food quality quite good. Compare to other hotels slight Costly.
Beautiful😍✨❤ …

This place is pure vegetarian !! It seems to be a Jain hotel  Hotel is decent but facilities are not up to the mark (might be coz of location )  No WiFi and lift was not working  Few rooms had no water and TV is not all working !!!!  Room size is ok but outdated furniture (can’t expect as well )  Over all “Ok” types and manageable
